properties.description:
If the navigation is in `megaMenu` mode it can to have two
levels of children instead of just one

If an anchor is needed, add an href prop to the last level item:
```
[{
 'label': 'my item',
 'isSelected': true, // preselects a nav item if necessary
 'children': [{
     'label': 'my sub item 1',
     'href': 'link sub item 1'
   }, {
     'label': 'my sub item 2',
     'href': 'link sub item 2'
   }
 ]
}]
```

A target prop can also be added to specify anchor target:
```
[{
 'label': 'my item',
 'isSelected': true, // preselects a nav item if necessary
 'children': [{
     'label': 'my sub item 1',
     'href': 'link sub item 1',
     'target': '_blank'
   }, {
     'label': 'my sub item 2',
     'href': 'link sub item 2',
     'target': '_blank'
   }
 ]
}]
```

Available targets are:
 * `_self`: the current browsing context. (Default)
 * `_blank`: usually a new tab, but users can configure browsers to open a new window instead.
 * `_parent`: the parent browsing context of the current one. If no parent, behaves as _self.
 * `_top`: the topmost browsing context (the "highest" context thatâ€™s an ancestor of the current one). If no ancestors, behaves as _self.

Note that href and target prop can be added to all nav items (first level included)
